
To do so, have a series of meetings with
your love interest.

During these meetings, you should attempt
to convince your love interest that you are
sincere and that the relationship would be
beneficial for all parties involved.

If the other party is willing, attempt to
secure a response through a series of meetings.

** Response to proposal of marriage
To do so, have a response to your proposal.
This response can be positive or negative.
If positive, continue with the process of
convincing your love interest that the
relationship would be functional and beneficial.
If negative, end the process and return to the state of being unmarried.














































